Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: GoogleScholar
Version: 0.2
Summary: Fetch information from Google Scholar
Home-page: https://github.com/lbello/chalmers-web/tree/master/scholar
Author: Luciano Bello
Author-email: luciano (a) debian (.) org
License: Do What the Fuck You Want to Public License
Description: At the moment, the module is mainly focus in authors information (aka
        citations).
        
        Search for authors (e.g. called "Bello" working for "Chalmers University"):
         >>> import scholar
         >>> l=scholar.searchAuthor('Bello Chalmers').next()
         >>> l.name
         <<< u'Luciano Bello'
        
        Fetch all the infmation of an author:
         >>> l.fillIn()
         >>> l.affiliation
         <<< u'PhD Student of Computer Science, Chalmers University of Technology'
        
        Get an author by id:
         >>> b=scholar.Author('L9Rk-_sAAAAJ')
         >>> b.fillIn()
         >>> b.citationIndex.all
         <<< 15
Platform: UNKNOWN
